task15

Manvydas Sokolovas

20 May 2016

Ukraunamas fpp paketas:

library("fpp")

1 uduotis:

Choose one of the following seasonal time series: condmilk, hsales, uselec

Naudojami uselec duomenys. Atvaizduojami grafikai:

plot(uselec, main = "Pradiniai duomenys")

hist(uselec, main = "Pradini duomen histograma")

  • Duomenys yra sezoniki, turi kylant trend.
  • Histograma panai normalaus skirstinio, taiau atrodo nepakankamai. Atliksime duomen transformacij.

(a) Do the data need transforming? If so, find a suitable transformation.

l <- BoxCox.lambda(uselec); l # Transformacijos lambda
## [1] -0.3468655
duom <- BoxCox(uselec, lambda = l)
plot(duom, col = "blue", main = "Duomenys po transformacijos")

hist(duom, main = "Transformuot duomen histograma")

  • Duomen transformacija sulygino duomen svyravimus ir taip pat matome, jog transformuot duomen histograma panaesn normaliojo skirstinio.

(b) Are the data stationary? If not, find an appropriate differencing which yields stationary data.

kpss.test(duom) # H0: duomenys yra stacionars
## Warning in kpss.test(duom): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  KPSS Test for Level Stationarity
## 
## data:  duom
## KPSS Level = 2.5736, Truncation lag parameter = 2, p-value = 0.01
  • p-value < 0.05, tai H0 hipotez atmetama. Duomenys nra stacionars.
n <- nsdiffs(duom); n
## [1] 1
duom2 <- diff(duom, diff = n)
plot(duom2, main = "Diferencijuot duomen grafikas")

kpss.test(duom2) # H0: duomenys yra stacionars
## Warning in kpss.test(duom2): p-value greater than printed p-value
## 
##  KPSS Test for Level Stationarity
## 
## data:  duom2
## KPSS Level = 0.0098762, Truncation lag parameter = 2, p-value =
## 0.1
  • Duomenys nebeturi trendo, todl panau, jog yra stacionars. KPSS testas patvirtina, jog duomenys yra stacionars (p-value > 0.05, H0 priimama).

(c) Identify a couple of ARIMA models that might be useful in describing the time series. Which of your models is the best according to their AIC values?

fit1 <- auto.arima(duom); fit1 # Gavome ARIMA(3,0,2)(2,1,0)[12] with drift
## Series: duom 
## ARIMA(3,0,2)(2,1,0)[12] with drift         
## 
## Coefficients:
##          ar1      ar2    ar3      ma1     ma2     sar1     sar2  drift
##       2.0405  -1.5632  0.458  -1.6535  0.8712  -0.4440  -0.4262  2e-04
## s.e.  0.1116   0.2075  0.108   0.0870  0.1095   0.0903   0.0871  1e-04
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 1.734e-05:  log likelihood=530.43
## AIC=-1042.85   AICc=-1041.35   BIC=-1017.05
fit2 <- arima(duom, order=c(1,0,2), seasonal=c(2,1,0))
fit3 <- arima(duom, order=c(0,2,9), seasonal=c(0,0,6))

Palyginamos modeli AIC reikms:

AIC(fit1)
## [1] -1042.853
AIC(fit2)
## [1] -1040.505
AIC(fit3)
## [1] -1040.252
  • Matome, jog geriausias modelis yra pirmasis (fit1) - ARIMA(3,0,2)(2,1,0)[12]. Jo Akaike kriterijaus reikm yra maiausia.

(d) Estimate the parameters of your best model and do diagnostic testing on the residuals. Do the residuals resemble white noise? If not, try to find another ARIMA model which fits better.

acf(fit1$res)

  • Panau, jog io modelio liekanos yra baltasis triukmas - tik viena linija kerta mlyn punktyr.

Spjim patikrinsime atlikdami Ljung-Box test su H0 hipoteze, jog liekanos yra baltasis triukmas:

Box.test(fit1$res, type = "Ljung")
## 
##  Box-Ljung test
## 
## data:  fit1$res
## X-squared = 0.0023653, df = 1, p-value = 0.9612
  • p-value > 0.05, tai H0 hipotez priimama. Liekanos yra baltasis triukmas.

(e) Forecast the next 24 months of data using your preferred model.

frc1 <- forecast(fit1, h = 24)
plot(frc1, main = "Modelio ARIMA(3,0,2)(2,1,0)[12] prognoz 24 mnesiams")

  • Prognoz atrodo logika.

(f) Compare the forecasts obtained using ets().

fit4 <- ets(duom)
plot(forecast(fit4, h = 24), main = "Modelio ETS(M,Ad,M) 24 mnsi prognoz")

  • Grafikai prognozs atrodo labai panaios.

Lyginamas modeli RMSE:

accuracy(fit1)[2]
## [1] 0.003859678
accuracy(fit4)[2]
## [1] 0.003540657
  • ets modelio RMSE neymiai maesnis, taigi is modelis ir yra tinkamesnis uselec duomenims prognozuoti.
